 in Albourne (Sussex). The placename in Bury has the same etymology as in 1 above, while the placename in Albourne may derive from Old English <i>hol</i> ‘hole, hollow’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’."],"variants":[{"name":"Hollands","meanings":["English: variant of   Holland  , especially 3, with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Dutch: genitivized form of   Holland  ."]},{"name":"Howland","meanings":["English: variant of   Holland  .","Americanized form of Norwegian   Hovland  .","History: Howland was the name of three Quaker brothers, original settlers in Marshfield, MA. They were from Huntingdonshire, England. The eldest, John Howland (<i>c.</i> 1593–1672) was a passenger on the <i>Mayflower</i>, servant to Gov. John Carver, who died in the first winter at Plymouth Colony."]},{"name":"Hollander","meanings":["Dutch (also <b>Den Hollander</b>), German (also <b>Holländer</b>), English, Swedish, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Holland (see   Holland   1)."]},{"name":"Holand","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Holland  .","Norwegian: habitational name from about twenty farmsteads so named, composed of Old Norse <i>hár</i> ‘high’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, field’, denoting a high-lying farm."]},{"name":"Aland","meanings":["Scandinavian (<b>Åland</b>): topographic name from the Åland Islands in the Gulf of Bothnia.","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>atte lande</i> (Old French <i>laund</i>) ‘dweller at the glade or pasture’, or sometimes perhaps, ‘dweller at the old cultivated land(s)’ from Old English <i>eald</i>, <i>ald</i> ‘old’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’."]},{"name":"Hollon","meanings":["English: altered form of   Holland  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary de Holland was born in 1153, in Up Holland, Lancashire, England. She married William de Columbers about 1170, in Hale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1181, in Halewood, Lancashire, England, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1153–1181":"1153–1181","1151–1177":"1151–1177","1177–1235":"1177–1235","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1235":"1235","1177":"1177","1153":"1153","1151":"1151","1181":"1181","Hale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Hale, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hale, Lancashire, England":"Hale, Lancashire, England","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Up Holland, Lancashire, England","Halewood, Lancashire, England":"Halewood, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1153–1181":"1153–1181","1151–1177":"1151–1177","1177–1235":"1177–1235","about 1170":"noin 1170","1235":"1235","1177":"1177","1153":"1153","1151":"1151","1181":"1181","Hale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Hale, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hale, Lancashire, England":"Hale, Lancashire, England","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Up Holland, Lancashire, England","Halewood, Lancashire, England":"Halewood, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1153–1181":"1153–1181","1151–1177":"1151–1177","1177–1235":"1177–1235","about 1170":"environ 1170","1235":"1235","1177":"1177","1153":"1153","1151":"1151","1181":"1181","Hale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Hale, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hale, Lancashire, England":"Hale, Lancashire, Angleterre","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Up Holland, Lancashire, Angleterre","Halewood, Lancashire, England":"Halewood, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mary de Holland est née en 1153, à Up Holland, Lancashire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé William de Columbers environ 1170, à Hale, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1181, à Halewood, Lancashire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 28 ans."},"de":{"1153–1181":"1153–1181","1151–1177":"1151–1177","1177–1235":"1177–1235","about 1170":"um 1170","1235":"1235","1177":"11